<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6253] Collapse SQLException factories</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6253</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Both the client driver and the embedded driver have factories that produce SQLExceptions of the correct sub-type. We don&apos;t need the factories that produce JDBC 3.0 exceptions now that the base level is JDBC 4.0.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12651646">DERBY-6253</key>
            <summary>Collapse SQLException factories</summary>
